President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate the following individuals for key positions in his administration:

1. Christopher Fall of Virginia: Nominated to be Director of the Office of Science at the Department of Energy. Dr. Fall is currently the Principal Deputy Director of the Advanced Research Projects Agency â€“ Energy. He has previously served in various roles at the Office of Naval Research and the White House Office of Science and Technology Policy. Dr. Fall holds a Ph.D. in Neuroscience and a B.S. in Mechanical Engineering from the University of Virginia.

2. Christine J. Toretti of Pennsylvania: Nominated to be Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Republic of Malta. Ms. Toretti is a businesswoman, philanthropist, and civic leader. She was the President and CEO of the S.W. Jack Drilling Company and has served on various advisory boards and committees. Ms. Toretti is also a Republican National Committeewoman from Pennsylvania and has been involved in initiatives to advance women in politics. She received her B.S. from the University of Virginia.

